tion&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My colleague, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/luebby42&#34;&gt;Karsten Lübke&lt;/a&gt;, first grade statistician, pointed me out to a paper …&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In 2018, the statistican Meng wrote a paper about biases in big data &lt;a href=&#34;https://projecteuclid.org/euclid.aoas/1532743473&#34;&gt;see here&lt;/a&gt;. In a nutshell, he argues that non-random samples will be worse when data is larger. Yes, you heard correctly: &lt;em&gt;Big data is bad data, if not randomly drawn&lt;/em&gt;. That’s bold a claim.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
